fields.label: 1. Do you feel that the university provides sufficient mental health support and resources for students?
fields.choices: Yes. there are plenty of mental health resources available.,No. I feel the support is limited or difficult to access.,I am unaware of the available mental health resources.,The mental health support is helpful; but there could be more options

fields.label: 2. Have you experienced stress or mental health challenges related to your studies or work, and do you feel supported by the university?
fields.choices: Yes. I’ve experienced stress and I felt supported by the university.,Yes. I’ve experienced stress but I didn’t feel supported.,No. I haven’t experienced stress or I manage it on my own.,I’m not sure if there’s enough support for everyone dealing with stress.

fields.label: 3. Are you aware of any mental health programs or services available to students or university staff?
fields.choices: Yes. I’m aware of several programs and services.,No. I’m not aware of any mental health services available.,I’ve heard of some programs but haven’t used them.,I’m unsure / having doubts about the mental health services offered.

fields.label: 4. Do you feel that mental health is prioritized and addressed within the university community?
fields.choices: Yes. mental health is a priority and efforts are visible.,No. I don’t think mental health is given enough attention.,I’ve seen some efforts but they don’t seem comprehensive.,I’m unsure as I haven’t seen much focus on mental health.

fields.label: 6. How comfortable do you feel speaking up against discrimination / injustice within the university?
fields.choices: Very comfortable -  I feel supported and encouraged to speak up.,Somewhat comfortable - but there could be more support.,Uncomfortable - I feel like speaking up may lead to consequences.,I don’t feel comfortable at all.

fields.label: 7. Do you feel that students/University staff from marginalized groups receive equal treatment and opportunities?
fields.choices: Yes. I believe everyone receives equal opportunities.,No. some groups do not receive equal treatment.,I’m unsure. I haven’t observed how others are treated.,I’ve heard others discuss it but I haven’t experienced it personally.

fields.label: 1. Do you think the curriculum is diverse and inclusive of different perspectives and cultures?
fields.choices: Yes. the curriculum includes diverse perspectives and cultures.,No. I feel it lacks diversity and inclusivity.,I haven’t noticed much focus on diversity.,I think there’s room for improvement in making it more inclusive.

fields.label: 2. Do you find the curriculum challenging, engaging, and relevant to your future career goals?
fields.choices: Yes. it is challenging and aligns well with my career goals.,No. I find it unengaging or irrelevant.,It’s somewhat engaging. but not entirely relevant.,I’m unsure as I haven’t fully explored the curriculum.

fields.label: 3. Do you feel that the curriculum promotes critical thinking and personal growth?
fields.choices: Yes. it encourages critical thinking and personal growth.,No. it feels more focused on memorization and exams.,I think it promotes some level of growth but not enough critical thinking.,I’m not sure as I haven’t reflected much on it.

fields.label: 4. Is there room for improvement in the curriculum to make it more applicable to real-world issues?
fields.choices: Yes. I think it could be more practical and applicable to real-world scenarios.,No. I feel the curriculum is already applicable to real-world issues.,There are areas that could be improved. but overall it’s okay.,I haven’t thought much about how applicable it is to real-world issues.

fields.label: 5. Do you feel that the curriculum adequately addresses the mental health and well-being of students?
fields.choices: Yes. there are elements within the curriculum that support mental health and well-being.,No. I don’t think mental health is addressed in the curriculum.,Some aspects touch on mental health. but it could be more prominent.,I’m unsure. as I haven’t seen mental health being directly addressed.

fields.label: Any messages, tips, or advice you would like to share that could help the reader/Kabsuhenyos?
